A very simple way of keeping your header at the top is adding position: sticky and top:0;

    header {
      background: purple;
      padding: 1rem;
      color: white;
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;

Try that and see if that works. Also, if you add position: sticky to another element below the first, it will take precedence of the original sticky element and make the new element the sticky one.
Here is a simple example of it. https://css-tricks.com/position-sticky-2/

